Performance
-----------

* kernel param: mitigations=off
  https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/Improving_performance#Turn_off_CPU_exploit_mitigations

* laptop
  w /sys/devices/system/cpu/cpufreq/policy*/energy_performance_preference - - - - performance

* fwupd-efi
  # Remove 10" delay
  sudo efibootmgr --delete-bootnum --bootnum 0001

* watchdog
  Add kernel parameter in/etc/default/grub:

  GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT="nowatchdog"

  Then blacklist the modules in /etc/modprobe.d/blacklist.conf:

  # Disable intel mei (including mei_watchdog).
  blacklist intel_pmc_bxt
  blacklist iTCO_vendor_support

  # Do not load the 'iTCO_wdt' watchdog module on boot.
  blacklist iTCO_wdt

* Makepkg Optimization
  https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/Makepkg#Optimization

  # CC
  /etc/makepkg.conf
  Remove any -march and -mtune flags, then add -march=native

  # Rust
  /etc/makepkg.conf.d/rust.conf
  RUSTFLAGS="-C force-frame-pointers=yes -C target-cpu=native"


Applications
------------
* Android studio - Use WLToolkit on wayland 
  modify Android studio desktop file:
  Exec=sh -c 'set -- "$@"; [ "$XDG_SESSION_TYPE" = wayland ] && set -- "$@" -Dawt.toolkit.name=WLToolkit; exec android-studio "$@"' sh %f

Various
-------
* set vconsole font:
  sudo vim /etc/vconsole.conf
  - ultrawide: 
    FONT=ter-120n
  - asus laptop:
    FONT=ter-128n

* set grub resolution:
  sudo vim /etc/default/grub
  - asus laptop:
    GRUB_GFXMODE=1920x1080

  ensure GRUB_GFXPAYLOAD_LINUX=keep is uncommented.

* (ASUS LAPTOP) 
  set < key to shift

  sudo vim /etc/udev/hwdb.d/99-custom-keyboard.hwdb
   
  add contents:
  # Remap keycode 93 (<) to Left Shift
  evdev:input:b*
   KEYBOARD_KEY_56=leftshift

  run:
  sudo systemd-hwdb update
  sudo udevadm trigger --verbose

* (ASUS LAPTOP)
  make hotkeys work without fn

  sudo vim /etc/default/grub
  GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT="asus_wmi.fnlock_default=0"

* (ASUS LAPTOP)
  disable fast boot in BIOS

* (ASUS LAPTOP)
  set headset as default at pavu

* add swapfile for limited memory systems(while keeping zram):
  sudo fallocate -l 16G /swapfile
  sudo chmod 600 /swapfile
  sudo mkswap /swapfile
  sudo swapon -p 10 /swapfile
  swapon --show (to confirm)

  Then add to /etc/fstab to make it permanent:
  /swapfile none swap defaults,pri=10 0 0


Brave Debloat
-------------
* UI Flags:
#brave-compact-horizontal-tabs

* Toolbar
Settings -> Appearance -> Customize your toolbar -> Disable all except "Forward" button

* Guides:
https://github.com/MulesGaming/brave-debloatinator/wiki/Additional-Resources#other-tools
https://github.com/libalpm64/Better-Brave-Browser/blob/main/README.md

